{
  "texts": [
    "Based on this data, machine-learning tools, such as penalised regression, are used to generate granular predictions for 'voter-types'also known as 'cells'.",
    "These predictions are then aggregated up to a desired geographic level of analysis, and released to the public.",
    "Examples of this practice are the various MrP forecasts by, for example, YouGov (Lauderdale and Blumenau 2019; Lauderdale 2019; Lauderdale et al. 2020).",
    "(2) A political campaign in the US wishes to optimise their use of financial resources, and target individuals and/ or areas to maximise their electoral returns.",
    "They purchase a 'Voter Registration' (VR) file from a vendor."
  ]
}